-- Silicor Receives $6 Million From Hudson Clean Energy Partners
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-09-04T18:11:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-04/silicor-receives-6-million-from-hudson-clean-energy-partners.html
Silicor Materials Inc., the closely
held polysilicon maker previously known as Calisolar Inc.,
received $6 million in additional funding from Hudson Clean
Energy Partners.  The capital will be used for operational costs as Silicor
plans for another funding round, assisted by Robert W. Baird &
Co., the San Jose, California-based company said today in a
statement. Silicor is building a $600 million factory in
 Mississippi  that is expected to reach full production capacity
of 16,000 metric tons a year in 2014.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Justin Doom in  New York  at 
 jdoom1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
